Let $AS=x$ and $SD=y$.

Since $\triangle SAP$ and $\triangle SDR$ are isosceles, then $AP=x$ and $DR=y$.

Since there are two pairs of identical triangles, then $BP=BQ=y$ and $CQ=CR=x$. [asy]
